A Study on the Unified Information Integration Platform of Railway Intermodal Transportation
SHI Yuanchao1, CHEN Cheng2 (1. Freight Department, China State Railway Group Co. Ltd., Beijing 100844, China; 2. Transportation & Economics Research Institute,
China Academy of Railway Sciences Co., Ltd., Beijing 100081, China)
Abstract: In intermodal transport, there is no data exchange or information sharing among the three main modes of transportation, namely railway, water transport and highway, which leads to the broken chain of logistics information, poor operation connection between different modes of transport, and low logistics efficiency in the whole process. Based on an overview of the positioning and objectives of the unified information integration platform of intermodal railway transportation with China State Railway Group at the core, this paper puts forward the overall design plan of the platform, which has defined its relationship with other platforms. To provide technical support for the establishment of the platform aiming to offer “one-stop” service supported by effective connectivity of various transportation modes, this paper has put forward the framework of the platform comprised of different function modules shared by China State Railway Group, and the external system. Keywords: Railway Freight Transportation; Intermodal Transportation; Logisitics; Information Integration; Platform Design
10

